election_record.label: Massachusetts 1792 Electoral College, Middle District

overview.note: A majority of votes was required to be elected. Only Azor Orne, Francis Dana and Increase Sumner received a majority of the votes. Thomas Dawes and Samuel Holton were subsequently selected by the Massachusetts General Court as the final two electors.

There were no affiliations or elector declarations in the Original Election Returns. Azor Orne, Francis Dana, Increase Sumner, Thomas Dawes and Samuel Holton voted for George Washington and John Adams in the Electoral College.
